.TH "drm_dev_alloc" 9 "drm_dev_alloc" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
drm_dev_alloc \- Allocate new DRM device
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct drm_device *" drm_dev_alloc
.BI "(const struct drm_driver *driver "  ","
.BI "struct device *parent "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "driver" 12
DRM driver to allocate device for
.IP "parent" 12
Parent device object
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This is the deprecated version of \fBdevm_drm_dev_alloc\fP, which does not support
subclassing through embedding the struct \fIdrm_device\fP in a driver private
structure, and which does not support automatic cleanup through devres.
.SH "RETURN"
Pointer to new DRM device, or ERR_PTR on failure.
